SIMPLE: stationer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stationer
<hw>Sta"tion*er</hw> <pr>(-⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Stationary</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A bookseller
or publisher; -- formerly so called from his occupying a stand, or
<xex>station</xex>, in the market place or elsewhere.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who sells paper, pens, quills, inkstands,
pencils, blank books, and other articles used in writing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stationery</ent>⟦br⟧
